criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        INCLUSION CRITERIA

          -  diagnosis of celiac disease according to ESPGHAN criteria: class III according to
             Marsh-Oberhuber classification, clear response to gluten-free diet, serological
             antiendomysium and antitransglutaminase antibodies positive results before GFD;

          -  HLA DQ2-DQ8 positive results;

          -  gluten-free diet from at least one year;

          -  negative serology from at least 1 year;

        EXCLUSION CRITERIA

          -  inflammatory bowel diseases;

          -  tumors;

          -  infectious liver disease;

          -  renal impairment.
